Canadian Imperial Bank Of Commerce (NYSE:CM) Receives An Update From Brokers


 By Ashley Brown /  in  Stocks /  on  Tuesday, 18 Jul 2017 07:55 AM  / 0 Comments




Analysts reviewing Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce have recently updated their recommended buy/sell ratings and price targets on the stock.  			         



Based on their most recently released notes to investors, 1 analyst has a rating of “buy”, 2 analysts “outperform”, 4 analysts “hold”, 3 analysts “underperform” and 0 analysts “sell”.
Ratings and price target breakdown:
 03/31/2017 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce was upgraded to “” by analysts at Credit Suisse.
 02/24/2017 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Keefe, Bruyette & Woods.
 12/02/2016 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at TD Securities. They now have a USD 115 price target on the stock.
 12/02/2016 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Scotiabank. They now have a USD 117 price target on the stock.
 12/02/2016 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at RBC Capital. They now have a USD 112 price target on the stock.
 11/01/2016 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Bank of America Merrill Lynch.
 09/21/2016 – Dundee Securities began new coverage on Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce giving the company a “” rating.
 08/26/2016 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Desjardins. They now have a USD 110 price target on the stock.
 08/26/2016 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at BMO Capital Markets. They now have a USD 103 price target on the stock.
 08/19/2016 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Barclays. They now have a USD 93 price target on the stock.
 06/30/2016 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Canaccord Genuity. They now have a USD 100 price target on the stock.
 12/07/2015 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce was downgraded to “” by analysts at Credit Agricole. They now have a USD 112 price target on the stock.
 12/04/2015 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at National Bank Financial. They now have a USD 100 price target on the stock.
 12/04/2015 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Macquarie. They now have a USD 78 price target on the stock.
 10/15/2015 – Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce had its “” rating reiterated by analysts at Beaufort Securities.
Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce has a 50 day moving average of 79.18 and a 200 day moving average of 83.77. The stock’s market capitalization is 34.15B, it has a 52-week low of 72.62 and a 52-week high of 92.22. 
The share price of the company (NYSE:CM) was down -0.51%, with a high of 85.73 during the day and the volume of Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce shares traded was 590720.  



Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce (CIBC) is a global financial institution. The Company provides a range of financial products and services to approximately 11 million individual, small business, commercial, corporate and institutional clients in Canada and around the world. The Company operates through three segments: Retail and Business Banking, Wealth Management and Capital Markets. The Company’s Retail and Business Banking segment provides personal and business clients across Canada with financial advice, products and services in its banking centers or through remote channels, such as mobile advisors, telephone, online or mobile banking. The Company’s Wealth Management segment provides advice and investment solutions. The Company’s Capital Markets segment provides integrated credit and global markets products, investment banking advisory services and research to corporate, government and institutional clients around the world.


